<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Website Downtime Alert</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h2 {
            color: #d9534f;
        }

        p {
            color: #333333;
        }

        .timestamp {
            color: #777777;
            font-size: 12px;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        a {
            color: #337ab7;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .footer {
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding-top: 10px;
            border-top: 1px solid #dddddd;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Website Downtime Alert</h2>
        <p>Hello <%=website.user.name %>,</p>
        <p>We regret to inform you that <%= website.name %> is currently experiencing downtime.</p>
        <p>This is an urgent notification from our website monitoring service. We have detected downtime on
            <%=website.name%>. Please take immediate action to investigate and resolve the issue.
        </p>
        <p>You can visit the website at: <a href=<%=website.url %>> <%=website.url %></a></p>
        <p>We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your patience.</p>
        <p class="timestamp">Timestamp: <%= Date.now()%>
        </p>
        <div class="footer">
            <p>This message was sent by the Downtime Reporter.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>